  "text": "The first publication on the new method was an observational study on the effect of the ILF training on chronic pain, in particular Complex Regional Pain Syndrome (CRPS1; [CITATION_1] . The second was a case series on combat-related PTSD [CITATION_2] . The third was a case series on pediatric epilepsy [CITATION_3] . A fourth publication considered the application of the method to pediatric neurology generally . Finally, the method is placed in its historical context, and described in considerable detail, in a more recent publication [CITATION_4] . Clinical data are shown for recovery from attentional deficits in a large cohort.",
